dataIdInfo.idAbs: Spatial and informational database of irrigated parcels in Division 6 of the Yampa/White Basins for the 2015 growing season in support of the CDSS.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: CDSS funded by Colorado Water Conservation Board (CWCB) and Colorado Division of Water Resources (CDWR). Input to dataset from various water users including water commissioners, ditch companies, water management groups, and individual farmers.

prcStep.stepDesc: The Division 6, year 2005 dataset was copied and used as a base for the 2010 dataset. The dataset was used in combination with the 2011 NAIP aerial imagery to refine field boundaries and identify additional potentially irrigated fields based on a visual assessment. Where applicable, 1993 and 2000 fields were added to accurately reflect conditions in 2010.

Multidate Landsat 5 images were composited and run through the NDVI model to obtain NDVI composites, which were then used to determine irrigated vs non-irrigated lands, and also where fields needed to be divided for potentially different crops. Ground truth fields were used to determine specific crop signatures using the NDVI composites, via the Zonal Statistics tool in ERDAS on each imagery date. These signatures were then combined in Excel and outliers were removed from the ground truth pool.

Imagery Classification: A supervised classification was run on the Landsat composite imagery using half of the ground truth fields. The remaining half was used for accuracy assessment. The Zonal Statistics tool in ERDAS was used to determine the Majority crop type for each parcel.

Crop Type assignment: Crop types were assigned based on the classified majority crop type in each parcel. Where satellite images overlapped, crop type was assigned based on the most accurate scene analysis. Fields initially determined to be fallow during the field boundary and NDVI review, or classified as fallow, were double checked for accuracy. Parcels noted as orchards in 1993 or 2005 were checked and reclassified as orchard where applicable, as well as those parcels notes as orchard during the field boundary review.

Additional updates were made to the 1993 dataset in 2014 as a result of investigations into diversions on major structures. Through discussions with water commissioners, changes were made to structure assignments and field boundaries. Additional lands were added where needed, and some lands were removed. Surface water COV fields were also removed from the dataset. Percentages associated with multiple structures on a parcel will be handled by the models and detailed in coding in HydroBase.

QA/QC The data was checked for topology errors, and final crop types were assigned from the classification work. In cases where crop type had been provided by the commissioners, that crop was treated the same as a ground truth parcel and assigned if it conflicted with the classified crop. Irrigated parcels were checked again in a QAQC procedure to ensure they comply with CDSS standards. This included checking all attributes including: all SW_COV attributes total 100, SW_WDID attributes are not duplicated, all SW_WDID attributes exist in the structure table of HydroBase. Edits and adjustments were made accordingly. All parcels comply with CDSS standards.
